<section class="p-6 bg-white shadow rounded-md mb-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Dashboard Overview</h1>
  <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
    The Dashboard is the central hub of your author account. It provides a comprehensive
    overview of all your content, audience engagement, and performance metrics in one place.
    This page allows you to quickly assess the health of your blog and make data-driven decisions.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Sections Included:</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
    <li><strong>Blog Count:</strong> Total number of articles you have published, including drafts and scheduled posts.</li>
    <li><strong>Views:</strong> Shows how many times your posts have been read. Helps track popular content.</li>
    <li><strong>Shares:</strong> Indicates how often readers are sharing your content on social media, helping gauge reach.</li>
    <li><strong>Comments:</strong> Displays engagement from your readers. More comments mean higher interaction and connection with your audience.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Graphs:</strong> Visual charts that show trends over time, such as views per post, monthly traffic, and top-performing articles.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Purpose of the Dashboard:</h2>
  <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
    The Dashboard helps you monitor the success of your content in real-time. By tracking metrics like views, shares, and comments, you can identify what resonates with your audience. This insight allows you to focus on high-performing topics, optimize your posting schedule, and grow your readership.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mt-4 mb-2">Why Each Section Matters:</h2>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 space-y-1">
    <li>Blog Count ensures you know how active you are as a creator and helps plan your publishing strategy.</li>
    <li>Views give insight into overall audience interest.</li>
    <li>Shares expand your content’s reach outside the platform.</li>
    <li>Comments provide qualitative feedback, helping you engage with readers directly.</li>
    <li>Performance Graphs help visualize trends, detect spikes or drops in engagement, and optimize content accordingly.</li>
  </ul>
</section>
